cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.DS 

The paper discusses a data-driven approach for modelling non-linear dynamical systems using Genetic Programming (GP) and Tree Adjoining Grammar. This involves the use of machine learning techniques and algorithms, which are typically covered under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with the modelling of physical systems, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method on three case studies, which involves the analysis of experimental data, and hence falls under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
